network_overview: The capture contains only IMS-SIP signaling for two VoLTE/VoNR call attempts that were both cancelled by the originator after ~16 s; no user-plane RTP or bearer-setup traffic is present. Every call leg ends with SIP 487 “Request Terminated” triggered by a user-initiated CANCEL, so the network delivered ringing but the caller hung up before answer.

observations.finding: 100 % of flows are SIP control-plane; zero GTP-U, RTP or Diameter packets seen, indicating the trace was filtered to IMS signalling only.
Both calls progressed to 180 Ringing (and 183 Session-Progress) but were cancelled at ~16 s; no RTP metrics available, so voice quality cannot be assessed.
Two SIP 407 Proxy Authentication Required responses were properly challenged and re-INVITEs sent; authentication is working, not a failure cause.
All six flows show SIP 487 Request Terminated with Q.850 cause 16 (normal call clearing) – failures are user behaviour, not network fault.

root_causes.description: Both INVITE transactions received 180 Ringing within ~1 s and were alive for ~16 s, then the UAC sent CANCEL; no 5xx or transport errors occurred.
root_causes.impact: Raises drop-call counters in OSS but is not a network defect; may still trigger customer complaints.

recommendations.action: Collect parallel RTP capture from SGi or S1-U to verify media was offered and ring-back tone was actually played to caller.
recommendations.rationale: Confirms whether long post-dial delay or missing early-media caused user to hang up.

recommendations.action: Check MMTel/AS logs for Alert-Timer (typically 30 s) to ensure network would not have forced release before answer.
recommendations.rationale: Rules out network-side expiry as contributor to abandonment.

recommendations.action: Add SIP P-Early-Media header if not present, and verify 183 responses carry valid SDP to accelerate ring-back delivery.
recommendations.rationale: Reduces perceived wait time and may lower cancellation rate.

session_analysis.signaling_health: Control-plane is stable: INVITE → 407 → ACK → re-INVITE → 100 → 183 → PRACK → 200 → 180 progressed correctly; no retransmissions or 5xx seen.
session_analysis.user_plane_health: No RTP or bearer-setup packets captured; QoS bearer must have been created earlier or on another interface.
session_analysis.voice_quality: No RTP statistics available; from SIP point of view early-media and ringing were delivered, so quality is assumed good until media stage.
session_analysis.cross_plane_correlation: Signaling reached alerting state but without corresponding RTP flow we cannot confirm ring-back reached the handset; correlate with S1-U or SGi RTP capture for full view.
